{
  "doc_id": "46028",
  "text": "Disruption of protein homeostasis, or proteostasis, is a hallmark of many neurodegenerative diseases, such as Alzheimer's disease and Parkinson's disease as well as HD. Proteostasis is the precise balance of protein expression in cells at the correct concentrations, in the correct localisation and with the appropriate conformation [CITATION_1] . Central to proteostasis is the post-translational modification of proteins, by covalent attachment of ubiquitin, ie, ubiquitylation (Figure 1 ) [CITATION_2] . Ubiquitylation is catalysed by a three-enzyme cascade comprised of a ubiquitin activating enzyme (E1), a conjugating enzyme (E2) and a ligase (E3). E3 ligases are believed to be key in substrate recognition. Several E3 ligases have been reported to ubiquitylate HTT, including WWP1 [CITATION_3] , UBE3A [CITATION_4] , HACE1 [CITATION_5] , CHIP [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] , Hrd1 [CITATION_8] and Parkin [CITATION_9] in mammals and Ltn1 [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] in yeast. Conjugated ubiquitin can be further modified at one of its seven lysine residues (K6, K11, K27, K29, K33, K48 and K63) as well as the N-terminal methionine (M1) to form polyubiquitin chains of different linkages [CITATION_12] . The covalently attached ubiquitin or ubiquitin chain can be removed by a family of enzymes called deubiquitylases (DUBs) . Surprisingly, few DUBs have been reported to deubiquitylate HTT. ATXN3, a DUB that itself contains a polyQ tract, and USP19 are the only known DUBs to target HTT [CITATION_13] [CITATION_14] [CITATION_15] besides UPS. Monoubiquitylation or ubiquitin conjugation of proteins by different linkages of chains are recognised by a range of proteins containing ubiquitin binding domains (UBDs) or ubiquitininteracting motifs (UIMs) and are essential in numerous cell signalling pathways. Ubiquitylated proteins can be targeted for degradation via the ubiquitin proteasome system (UPS) or lysosome/autophagy pathways. Ubiquitin-like modification, such as sumoylation [CITATION_16] , is also known to play critical role of HTT degradation.",
